radiographic_examinations.findings: Identified 13 dental ageneses, including the upper central incisor, upper first premolars, upper and lower second premolars, lower second molars, and upper and lower third molars, characterizing oligodontia. CBCT images showed the position of the permanent lower canines in buccally displaced. The single median maxillary central incisor (SMMCI) was positioned practically in the midpalatal raphe.
